      • getDefaultValueString

        private String getDefaultValueString​(Class token)
        Return default value with leading space for passed token conversed to string.

        Return " 0" for primitives, " false" for boolean and " null" for object references. If passed class is null, empty string returned.

        Parameters:
        token - class to get default value
        Returns:
        class default value string with single space.

      • cleanModifiers

        private String cleanModifiers​(int modifier)
        Returns modifier without transient and abstract tags converted to string.
        Parameters:
        modifier - modifier to be converted
        Returns:
        string which consists of all other modifiers

      • checkParameters

        private void checkParameters​(Class<?> token,
                             Path root)
                      throws ImplerException
        Checks if any of passed parameters is incorrect or null, otherwise an exception is thrown.
        Parameters:

        root - second parameter
        Throws:

      • writePackage

        private void writePackage​()
                   throws IOException
        Writes package info.

        Writes information about package of the stored class token in standard format to the corresponding java file created for the class using stored writer.

        Throws:
        IOException - if error occurs while writing

      • writeHeading

        private void writeHeading​()
                   throws IOException
        Writes class heading.

        Writes information about the stored class token using stored writer. Generated class extends token class and named same but with "Impl" prefix.

        Throws:
        IOException - if error occurs while writing

      • writeMethods

        private void writeMethods​()
                   throws IOException
        Implements methods that will return default values.

        Writes an implementation for abstract and interface methods of the stored class token in the java file using stored writer. Methods that have been already implemented in ancestors will be added.

        Throws:
        IOException - if error occurs while writing
        See Also:
        getDefaultValueString(Class), clearMethodsClass(Class, Set)

      • implementConstructors

        private boolean implementConstructors​()
                               throws IOException
        Writes default implementation of constructors. Writes non-private constructors of the stored class token in the java file using stored writer. Implemented constructors do nothing but call super-constructors with same arguments.
        Returns:
        true if at least one constructor has been implemented
        Throws:
        IOException - if error occurs while writing

      • addArgs

        private void addArgs​(Class<?>[] args,
                     boolean printNames)
              throws IOException
        Writes args names in line.

        Writes args names in line divided by commas and spaces to the java file using stored writer. If printNames is true also adds names arg1, arg2, arg3, ... after class names.

        Parameters:
        args - array of classes which names should be written
        printNames - controls writing names after class names
        Throws:
        IOException - if error occurs while writing

      • implementJar

        public void implementJar​(Class<?> token,
                         Path root)
                  throws ImplerException
        Produces .jar file implementing class or interface specified by provided token.

        Generated class full name should be same as full name of the type token with Impl suffix added.

        Specified by:
        implementJar in interface JarImpler
        Parameters:
        token - type token to create implementation for.
        root - target .jar file.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - if an error occurred during implementation or generating jar
        See Also:
        implement(Class, Path)

      • implement

        public void implement​(Class<?> token,
                      Path root)
               throws ImplerException
        Produces java file for class with default implementation.

        Produces java file for token in passed path root with default implementation. token cannot be generic, abstract, array or final. Passed class should have at least one non-private constructor if it is not an interface.

        Specified by:
        implement in interface Impler
        Parameters:
        token - class token to create implementation for.
        root - root directory.
        Throws:
        ImplerException - is thrown if an error occurs during implementation

      • main

        public static void main​(String[] args)
        Runs implementor in specified mode with arguments passed with args. Arguments format: [-jar] . use -jar parameter for implementing jar file. If an error occurs implementing is stopped and error is shown on the screen.
        Parameters:
        args - arguments passed
        See Also:
        implement(Class, Path), implementJar(Class, Path)
